Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In Chelsea, a two-bedroom, one-bath apartment with prewar details like crystal doorknobs and a claw-foot bathtub, in a 1917 walk-up building.
• In Midtown, a two-bedroom, two-bath apartment with many custom finishes in Ritz Tower, a full-service co-op designed by Emery Roth.
• In Park Slope, Brooklyn, a one-and-a-half-bath duplex with a below-grade sleeping area, a wood-burning fireplace and a walk-in laundry room in a five-unit self managed, cat-friendly brownstone co-op.
